---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";
import EpisodeSequencePlate from "../components/EpisodeSequencePlate.astro";
import EpisodePartStructure from "../components/EpisodePartStructure.astro";
import EpisodeAnchorsIndex from "../components/EpisodeAnchorsIndex.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<Layout title="Episodes" description="The seventy-three episodes of Gravity's Rainbow, treated as a formal sequence.">
  <Nav slot="nav" />

  <Section>
    <div class="page-head reveal visible">
      <p class="eyebrow">01</p>
      <h1>The seventy-three episodes</h1>
      <div class="page-lede">
        <p>
          <em>Gravity's Rainbow</em> is treated here as a sequence of seventy-three
          formal units. The score shows how plot machinery gathers, stalls, and
          disperses across the four parts: not a table of contents, but a map of
          narrative pressure.
        </p>
        <p>
          Uneven scale matters because the novel does not distribute attention
          evenly. Blicero and Gottfried, Roger and Jessica, Slothrop, Pökler,
          Tchitcherine, Byron, and the final descent do not simply occupy
          episodes; they change the tempo of reading around the Rocket.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <section class="plate-break reveal visible">
    <div class="plate-container">
      <figure class="episode-figure">
        <EpisodeSequencePlate />
      </figure>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <figcaption class="plate-caption">
        Every mark is one episode in reading order. Height carries word count;
        interior ticks carry paragraph structure; baseline marks identify public
        anchors. The plate makes visible where the book expands into systems,
        where it cuts into quick fragments, and where the Rocket moves from
        object to apparatus.
      </figcaption>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Section narrow={true}>
    <div class="prose-block reveal visible">
      <p>
        Part III is the hinge. Its expansion changes the reader's experience from
        pursuit through wartime plots into navigation through the Zone, where
        Slothrop's line begins to scatter and other systems take over. The late
        book then turns that dispersal into ritual, media, infrastructure, and
        terminal descent.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <section class="plate-break reveal visible">
    <div class="plate-container">
      <figure class="episode-figure">
        <EpisodePartStructure />
      </figure>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <figcaption class="plate-caption">
        Part-level structure summarised from the same public-safe metadata. The
        movement trace preserves episode order within each part, showing how the
        novel shifts from London machinery to casino pursuit, Zone expansion,
        and final convergence.
      </figcaption>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Section narrow={true}>
    <div class="anchor-block reveal visible">
      <p class="eyebrow">Episode anchors</p>
      <p>
        The anchor layer names selected pressure points in the score: plot
        pivots, system revelations, counter-quests, comic infrastructure, and
        the final convergence of Rocket, ritual, cinema, and apocalypse. Where a
        short quotation has been manually approved, it remains secondary to the
        site's commentary.
      </p>
      <EpisodeAnchorsIndex />
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section narrow={true}>
    <div class="notes-block reveal visible">
      <p class="eyebrow">Notes</p>
      <ol class="notes-list">
        <li>
          The episode layer uses only the public-safe metadata export:
          global order, episode ID, part, part title, word count, and paragraph
          count. No source text, snippets, quotations, descriptions, or evidence
          fields are present.
        </li>
        <li>
          The imported CSV is logged in <code>data/provenance.md</code>. It is
          served from
          <a href={`${base}/data/base/episode_metadata_public.csv`}>public/data/base/episode_metadata_public.csv</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          The anchor and quote layers are served from
          <a href={`${base}/data/base/episode_anchors_public.csv`}>public/data/base/episode_anchors_public.csv</a>
          and
          <a href={`${base}/data/base/episode_anchor_quotes_public.csv`}>public/data/base/episode_anchor_quotes_public.csv</a>.
          The quote layer is sparse, manually approved, and contains no private
          source pointers, context windows, or bulk source text.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, 2.5rem);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .page-lede {
    max-width: var(--max-width-narrow);
  }

  .page-lede p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .plate-break {
    padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
  }

  .plate-container {
    max-width: min(98vw, 96rem);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--space-lg);
  }

  .episode-figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .plate-caption {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    max-width: var(--max-width-narrow);
  }

  .prose-block p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    max-width: var(--max-width-narrow);
  }

  .anchor-block {
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .anchor-block p:not(.eyebrow) {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    max-width: var(--max-width-narrow);
  }

  .notes-block {
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  @media (max-width: 48rem) {
    .plate-container {
      max-width: 100vw;
      padding: 0 var(--space-md);
    }
  }

  .notes-list {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    padding-left: 1.5em;
    list-style: decimal;
  }

  .notes-list li {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .notes-list li a {
    color: var(--color-accent-dim);
  }

  .notes-list li a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .notes-list code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9em;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }
</style>
